Look at the previous image.

Preserve the communication goal, customer takeaway, and information density.
Do not preserve the layout, composition, framing, or spatial structure.

The redesign should feel like a different premium designer created the image from scratch while preserving the same buyer-facing message.

Preserve the MESSAGE, not the geometry.
Avoid small cosmetic changes.
The redesign should introduce a noticeably different visual execution at first glance.

Keep the redesign: premium, visually original, communication-first.
Return markdown text only.
`.trim();

